<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>tutorial | lazappi</title><link>lazappi.id.au/tags/tutorial/</link><atom:link href="lazappi.id.au/tags/tutorial/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>tutorial</description><generator>Source Themes Academic (https://sourcethemes.com/academic/)</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>© Luke Zappia, 2021</copyright><lastBuildDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2020 13:31:20 +0200</lastBuildDate><image><url>lazappi.id.au/img/icon.png</url><title>tutorial</title><link>lazappi.id.au/tags/tutorial/</link></image><item><title>Scanpy in R</title><link>lazappi.id.au/project/scanpy-in-r/</link><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2020 13:31:20 +0200</pubDate><guid>lazappi.id.au/project/scanpy-in-r/</guid><description>&lt;p>This tutorial covers how to set up a environment that lets you interact with
&lt;a href="https://scanpy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Scanpy&lt;/a> from R. This includes
converting Python
&lt;a href="https://anndata.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AnnData objects&lt;/a>
to R
&lt;a href="https://bioconductor.org/packages/release/bioc/html/SingleCellExperiment.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SingleCellExperiment&lt;/a>
and
&lt;a href="https://satijalab.org/seurat/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Seurat&lt;/a> objects as well as interacting with
a Python environment directly in an
&lt;a href="https://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">R Markdown&lt;/a>
document. It demonstrates some of the functions in Scanpy but doesn&amp;rsquo;t cover
everything the package can do or how best to use Scanpy for your analysis.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>